Interface Lens.Simple<S,A>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of both "larger" values
    A - the type of both "smaller" values
    All Superinterfaces:
    Functor<S>, Lens<S,S,A,A>
    Enclosing interface:
    Lens<S,T,A,B>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface Lens.Simple<S,A>
extends Lens<S,S,A,A>
    A convenience type with a simplified type signature for common lenses with both unified "larger" values and unified "smaller" values.

        Description copied from interface: Lens
        Fix this lens against some functor, producing a non-polymorphic runnable lens as an Fn2.

        Although the Java type system does not allow enforceability, the functor instance FT should be the same as FB, only differentiating in their parameters.
